Privacy Policy for WaterLife!

Effective Date: [May 25, 2025]

1. Introduction

Welcome to WaterLife! ("we," "our," or "us"). We are committed to protecting your personal information and your right to privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application.

By using WaterLife!, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with these terms, please do not use the app.

2. Information We Collect

We may collect the following types of information:

Personal Information: Such as your name and email address, when you voluntarily provide it to us.

Hydration Data: Information you input regarding your water intake and related habits.

Device Information: Including your device's model, operating system, and unique identifiers.

Usage Data: Information about how you use our app, including features accessed and time spent.

3. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information to:

Provide and maintain our services.

Personalize your experience and offer tailored features.

Monitor and analyze usage to improve our app.

Communicate with you about updates and other relevant information.

4. Sharing Your Information

We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your information with:

Service Providers: Third-party vendors who assist in operating our app and services.

Legal Authorities: When required by law or to protect our rights and safety.

5. Data Retention

We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.

6. Security of Your Information

We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

7. Children's Privacy

WaterLife! is intended for users of all ages. However, for users under the age of 13, parental discretion is advised. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without parental consent. We hold no liability whatsoever for the use of the app, and it is the absolute responsibility of the children's parents or guardians. 

8. User Responsibility and Disclaimer

Personal Responsibility: Users are solely responsible for how they use WaterLife! and for any decisions made based on the information provided by the app.

No Medical Advice: WaterLife! is intended for informational purposes only and does not constitute medical advice. Always consult a healthcare professional for medical concerns.

Limitation of Liability: The developer of WaterLife! shall not be held liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising out of your use of the app. Use of the app is at your own risk.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the new policy on this page and updating the effective date.

10. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us through the contact us form within the app.
